Product name: Vintage Stoneware Butter Churn/Antique Butter Churn/Vintage Louisville Pottery #3 Churn/Louisville Pottery Cherokee Churn/Antique Churn
Description:
This Stoneware Louisville Pottery #3 Butter Churn is from the Cherokee Line of Louisville Pottery, made between 1906 and 1938.  The Louisville Pottery Company began business in 1815  and began to supply Stoneware to the pioneers heading west.  Stoneware containers, which were the "Tupperware" of their day, were for storage of the supplies they carried on their journey.  Stoneware was the predominant pottery of the United States from the 1700's through the turn of the 20th century.  Stoneware is very hard, made from fine, dense clay and fired at a high temperature.  The glaze was produced by throwing salt into a kiln of the pottery at high heat.
This #3 Butter Churn is a 3 gallon container, that was originally intended for the churning of milk into butter.  This  Stoneware Churn is 14" High and has a 9" Diameter.  The churn has seen the use of time, which is evident with various nicks and scratches, as well as paint marks from a careless painter at some time in the past.  The churn paddle and handle have a variation in color.  The darkened part of the handle has been exposed to normal usage and exposure over the years, while the lower portion and paddle have been resting in the interior of the churn. 
 If you have any questions please Convo us. We always want to give you all possible information and pictures, so that you are fully familiar with the item. Because our items are all vintage and will have age related nicks, dings, tarnish, etc. we want you to be sure this is the item you want before ordering.

Product name: 25 Funeral Remembrance Balloons (choose from 10 colours). Biodegradable, Eco friendly, Memorial, Celebration of Life.
Description:
** 25 BIODEGRADABLE REMEMBRANCE BALLOONS **
A pack of 25 biodegradable Remembrance Balloons printed with the message 'You are Loved, You are Missed, You are Remembered'. These are available in 10 colours - white, red, orange, yellow, green, blue, purple, pale pink, bright pink and rainbow mix.
Ideal for releasing at funerals, celebrations of life, or on the anniversary of the passing of a loved one. They look wonderful released en masse and create a thoughtful, peaceful moment to mark the end of a funeral service or celebration of life.
These 12" latex balloons are 100% biodegradable and are suitable for helium or air inflation, making them ideal for balloon releases. The natural latex will decompose in roughly the same amount of time as an oak leaf.
Please note that it is not possible to personalize these balloons and they are only available in white.
These remembrance balloons are exclusive to Angel & Dove.
** SHIPPING **
All items are shipped from the United Kingdom. We ship daily to the US and worldwide.
STANDARD SHIPPING TO USA - untracked service with delivery aim of 6-8 working days via Royal Mail standard international air mail. Ideal for low value, non urgent orders without a deadline. 
EXPRESS SHIPPING TO USA - delivery in 2-3 working days via DHL Express courier. Recommended for higher value orders (over 20) with a deadline, this service offers faster customs clearance, online tracking and signature on delivery. Please select Shipping Upgrade at the checkout. 
UK SHIPPING - this item is shipped by second class post, so please allow 2-3 working days for delivery.  You can upgrade to First Class (1-2 working days) or First Class Signed For if you wish. Please select Shipping Upgrade at the checkout.
** ABOUT OUR BIODEGRADABLE BALLOONS **
These balloons are suitable for air or helium inflation. Helium gas not included. While disposable party helium canisters are readily available, we would recommend using a professional balloon or party shop to fill your balloons with helium. Please take care not to over-inflate balloons as this could cause them to pop. Keep out of the reach of children. Adults should fill balloons and supervise children under 8 years old. Not suitable for children under 3 years due to small parts.
 
What are they made from?
These balloons are 100% biodegradable, made in the UK from premium quality natural latex. The latex is produced from the sap of the rubber tree. It is collected without harming the tree using an age-old, environmentally safe process similar to that used for collecting the sap from maple trees for making syrup.
 
How are they biodegradable?
Stress caused by inflation starts the decomposition cycle and exposure to sunlight accelerates the process. During a balloon release, most balloons will rise to approximately 5 miles, where they oxidise, freeze and then shatter into tiny pieces. Research has shown that under the same conditions, latex decomposes as quickly as an oak leaf.
** GOOD PRACTICE FOR BALLOON RELEASES **
Only use biodegradable balloons and specially designed compostable seals to tie your balloons. Do not use standard plastic helium balloon valves or curling balloon string as these are no biodegradable. Balloons should be released individually and not tied together in order to protect wildlife and the environment. We recommend releasing your balloons within 4 hours of inflation for maximum height and float time.
** RETURNS **
Unsuitable items may be returned in their original packaging within 14 days of purchase, at the buyers expense (except where an item is faulty or damaged). If you need to return an item, please convo me first so that I can assist you further.

Product name: Nude coffin nails, Nail designs, Nail art, Nails, Stiletto nails, Acrylic nails, coffin nails, Fake nails, False nails
Description:
How to measure your nails: 
Cut a small strip of tape (scotch tape or masking tape - I prefer masking tape) and apply across the widest part of the nail. Make sure you press the tape into the sides of your nail! Use a pen and mark on each side of your nail. Peel off and measure (mm) with a ruler.
You can also measure your nails with a soft measuring tape, but personally I find it a bit too fiddly. 
XXS: Thumb 14mm, Pointer 11mm, Middle 11mm, Ring 10mm, Pinkie 9mm.
XS: Thumb 15mm, Pointer 12mm, Middle 12mm, Ring 11mm, Pinkie 9mm.
S: Thumb 17mm, Pointer 13mm, Middle 13mm, Ring 12mm, Pinkie 10mm.
M: Thumb 18mm, Pointer 14mm, Middle 14mm, Ring 13mm, Pinkie 10mm.
L: Thumb 19mm, Pointer 15mm, Middle 15mm, Ring 14mm, Pinkie 12mm.
If you don't fit within my size chart select the size CUSTOM and leave your nail measurements (mm) in the notes to seller section. Please note my largest nail size is 19mm wide and smallest is 9mm wide.
Sets of 20 - the set of 20 nails include 2 of each nail size!
For first time buyers I recommend purchasing a set of 20 nails - these sets include 2 nails of each size. This way you can find out your nail size without the hassle of measuring your nails. 
If you know your nail size by the nail number (the number under the tip of the nail) please select the size custom and leave your nail numbers in the notes to seller. 
Frequently asked questions: 
Do these nails come with glue?
No, due to shipping restrictions I cannot ship glue. Nail adhesive tabs are available to purchase on my store: 
www.etsy.com/uk/listing/469290949/nail-adhesive-tabs
What nail glue do you recommend? 
I recommend using the elegant touch super nail adhesive tabs - you can get these from my store, boots and many supermarkets.
How long do they last? 
How long they last really depends on how you take care of the nails. As long as you don't use your nails as tools and submerge them in water for long periods of time they last about 7 days. Using elegant touch super nail adhesive tabs I can keep the nails on for 10 days! 
Do they damage your natural nails? 
False nails do not damage your nails - it's how you remove the false nails! Nail adhesive tabs are easy to remove and don't damage your nails. Nail glue is harder to remove - rushing removing nails applied with nail glue can cause damage. If you are worried about damaging your nails, use nail adhesive tabs.
How do I apply false nails? 
Nail adhesive tabs; start with clean hands and apply the nail tabs to your nails, peel off the protective film and apply the false nail on top. 
Nail glue; start with clean hands apply one drop of nail glue to your natural nail, make sure you don't add too much. Press the false nail on top of your nail and hold for 10 seconds.
How do I remove false nails? 
Nail adhesive tabs; soak your nails in water for 5-10 mins and gently pry of the nails with an orange wood stick. 
Nail glue; soak the nails off with acetone. 
Can I get these nails shorter/longer? 
Yes but there is an additional fee.
Are these nails reusable? 
Yes these nails are reusable if you use nail adhesive tabs - as you can just roll the nail adhesive tab off the false nail and wear them again. 
How many nails do I get in each set? 
10 nails unless you select the set of 20.
Are these gel nails? 
No, I use a high quality gel effect topcoat.
Are these acrylic nails? 
No. 
Can I get my order made and shipped out ASAP? 
Yes please purchase 'rush order'. 
www.etsy.com/uk/listing/469289423/rush-order
How long does shipping take? 
Shipping to the UK; delivery aim 2 business days but it can take longer during busy periods.
Worldwide shipping; delivery aim 5 business days but it can take longer (I find it usually takes about 12 business days to arrive). Royal Mail states to wait 30 business days for a worldwide order to arrive before filling out a lost parcel form. 
Do you do custom designs?
 Yes! Just send me a message or press the blue ‘request a custom order’ button.
Do you give discount for wholesale orders?
 Yes I give 15% off orders over £200 with this promotion code: WHOLESALEPLP
Do you have a promotion code?
 Yes you get 10% off orders over £60 with this promotion code: PROMO10PLP
Can I cancel my order? 
Orders can only be cancelled within 20 minutes of purchase. This is because all my orders are custom made and cannot be resold.
Can I return or exchange my order? 
Due to all my items being custom made, returns and exchanges are not possible.
Please note all nails are modelled in size XXS.  Whether you order XXS, XS, S, M or L nails, all nails will be made exactly as the photos portray. However, please expect differences due purely to the difference in size.  For example, an XXS nail does look different to say a L nail.

Product name: MS Awareness Bracelet, Leukemia Awareness Bracelet, CRPS Awareness Bracelet with orange ribbon charm
Description:
This listing is for an orange MS Awarness bracelet, although the colour orange  can also represent other conditions, such as Leukemia and CRPS. 
Awareness Ribbons, a commonly seen 21st Century  phenomenon, were created to  increase general public awareness of a particular illness, disability or condition, and to gather support for its sufferers. 
It is a simple way to show your support for a specific cause, or perhaps even to indicate that you are suffering from that particular condition yourself. 
Every day, new coloured ribbons are added to the growing list of internationally recognised conditions, and have often become synonymous with the condition itself eg the pink ribbon which denotes breast cancer awareness. 
This MS Awareness bracelet is made from orange faux suede,  representing Multiple Sclerosis, Leukemia or CRPS. 
The bracelet is available in a range of sizes via the drop down menu, and is fully adjustable with an extension chain. Just let me know if you require a size that is not listed, by contacting me via the 'Message to Seller' option. 
The suede band attaches to an infinity symbol, to represent the universality of the condition, and to emphasise that this condition is something that affects the sufferer each minute of each hour of each and every day. Alternatively, you can choose to replace the infinity symbol with an affirmation ring with the word STRENGTH stamped on it, to represent the fight that sufferers battle through on a daily basis, see listing photo for examples of these different options. 
Finally, a charm is added as a finishing touch.  
You can choose an orange enamelled awareness ribbon, a plain silver awareness ribbon, a silver 'hope' ribbon. Perhaps you may prefer a 'spoony' charm, which refers to the 'Spoon Theory' an explanation to help others understand how living with a chronic condition can affect a sufferer.
Please choose your preferences from the drop down menu, and select your charm.
